# SnapPath - Cursor Rules

> See `CLAUDE.md` for complete project documentation.

## Project Context

macOS menu bar screenshot utility (SwiftUI). Captures screenshots and copies file paths to clipboard.

## Build Commands

```bash
# Build
xcodebuild -project SnapPath.xcodeproj -scheme SnapPath -configuration Debug build
```

## Architecture Notes

- Service-oriented architecture
- No App Sandbox (required for screen capture)
- Menu bar only app (no Dock icon)
- Uses `KeyboardShortcuts` and `LaunchAtLogin` packages

## Code Style

- Swift 5.0
- SwiftUI for UI
- `@AppStorage` for settings persistence
- Services in `Services/` folder, Views in `Views/` folder

## Important Files

- `SnapPathApp.swift` - Entry point
- `Services/HotkeyService.swift` - Global shortcuts
- `Models/AppSettings.swift` - Settings
- `Info.plist` - Must include `NSScreenCaptureUsageDescription`

